{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_013Qe1ZtaLPrt6xNbUQs2EJK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything checks out. Summary of the fix:\n\n- **Root cause**: `prometheus-config` ConfigMap only had a `localhost:9090` self-scrape job — nothing pointed at RabbitMQ. RabbitMQ itself was already correctly configured (plugin enabled, port 15692 exposed on the `rabbitmq`/`rabbitmq-headless` Services).\n- **Fix**: Patched `prometheus-config` (native ConfigMap, no CRDs) to add a `rabbitmq` scrape job with static targets for the 3 stable per-pod DNS names via the headless Service (`rabbitmq-{0,1,2}.rabbitmq-headless.<ns>.svc.cluster.local:15692`), plus a `rules.yml` recording rule (`rabbitmq_up = up{job=\"rabbitmq\"}`) since the RabbitMQ Prometheus plugin doesn't itself expose a metric literally named `rabbitmq_up`.\n- **Applied via** `kubectl apply` + `/-/reload` (enabled via `--web.enable-lifecycle`) — no pod restarts needed.\n- **Verified**: all 3 RabbitMQ targets show `health: up`, `rabbitmq_up` query returns 3 samples (all value `1`), and `rabbitmqctl cluster_status` confirms the 3-node cluster is still fully healthy."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1734,"cache_read_input_tokens":57550,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1734},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"21eeb6ec-c015-40f6-bcd8-f93b760804d6","uuid":"739eb322-8134-4979-ade0-b917badc64e3","request_id":"req_011CcahLkh5ehZFS72Jv729R"}
